

15,01                             Chained to the Glow

15,01                      00Slave to the prime-time patriarch
15,01                      00Ensnared by the hypnotic glow
15,01                      00Of phosphorous and false smiles.
15,01                      00Your soap-opera saviors absolve you of sin
15,01                      00And fill you with distorted truths.
15,01                      00Trapped in a glass box, screaming like a mime,
15,01                      00Your mind becones a prisoner of complacency.
15,01                      00Resting only to revel within in the confines
15,01                      00Of the regent refrigerator.
15,01                      00You drag along the dusty road of life
15,01                      00Like a dead-end sitcom.


